Celso Jos√© da Costa (born April 7, 1949 in Congonhinhas) is a Brazilian mathematician working in differential geometry. His research activity has focused in the construction and classification of minimal surfaces embedded in three-dimensional Euclidean space. He is best known for his discovery of Costa's minimal surface, which was described in 1982.
He earned his Ph.D. from IMPA in 1982 under the supervision of Manfredo do Carmo.


